main_body:
Sources and methods to compile quarterly data
The compilation of quarterly data for the categories referred to in Article 2 shall respect the following rules:
1. quarterly data shall be based on direct information available from basic sources, such as for example public accounts or administrative sources, representing, for each category, at last 90 % of the amount of the category;
2. direct information shall be completed by coverage adjustments, if needed, and by conceptual adjustments in order to bring quarterly data in line with ESA 95 concepts;
3. the quarterly data and the corresponding annual data shall be consistent.
